    • Uses of Cleanable in fr.sii.ogham.sms.sender.impl.cloudhopper.session

      Subinterfaces of Cleanable in fr.sii.ogham.sms.sender.impl.cloudhopper.session 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  SessionHandlingStrategy
      There exists several ways to manage SMPP session between the client and the server: A new session can be created for each message (useful when message needs to be sent only sometimes) A session can be reused if possible until no message has been sent for a while (useful when several messages have to be sent in a row) Keep the session always alive (useful when application needs to send messages quickly and often) ... This interface defines the entrypoints that need to be implemented to handle a session.
      Classes in fr.sii.ogham.sms.sender.impl.cloudhopper.session that implement Cleanable 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AlwaysNewSessionStrategy
      Simple management of SMPP session.
      class  BaseSessionHandlingStrategy
      Base class for different session handling strategies.
      class  KeepSessionAliveStrategy
      Strategy that regularly sends EnquireLink requests to keep session alive.
      class  MayReuseSessionStrategy
      Strategy that attempts to reuse the previous session if possible.
